{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Kaplan et al.",
    "show in their study on scaling laws that the crossentropy loss correlates with dataset size, computational power, and the number of parameters [16].",
    "The research team of Google Deepmind found that training data should be scaled together with the model size [12].",
    "Notably, GPT-3 showcased the improved few-shot performance of LLM [3], and public attention peaked with the introduction of ChatGPT in 2022.",
    "A competing chat system based on LLM is Google Bard, which initially used Language Model for Dialogue Applications (LaMDA) [24], a 137-billion parameter model."
  ],
